            <title>[LU-3034] do not define HAVE_SERVER_SUPPORT when compiling liblustre</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3034</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From the discussion on &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/2675&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/2675&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Andreas Dilger has posted comments on this change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Change subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1330&quot; title=&quot;split/cleanup for obdclass/fid/fld modules&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1330&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1330&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fld: prepare FLD module for client server split&lt;br/&gt;
......................................................................&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch Set 12: Looks good to me, approved&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unrelated to this path directly, but is like to get a fix to the configure code so that HAVE_SERVER_SUPPORT is not defined for liblustre. That avoids the need to check both. _&lt;em&gt;KERNEL&lt;/em&gt;_ and HAVE_SERVER_SUPPORT for the conditional code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
